            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "We might want to do some validation here. A quick scan of `curl(1)` gives us the following concerns:\r\n- Any keys that start with `@` will be treated as filenames by curl.\r\n- Some control characters may be problematic.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, `curl` has a special meaning for an empty `value` which we will want to override by using a semicolon when an empty value is provided (see manual page for details). This means we will want to do the following, in addition to validation:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nif value == '' then\r\n  vim.list_extend(args, { '-H', key .. ';' })\r\nelse\r\n  vim.list_extend(args, { '-H', key .. ': ' .. value })\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nSorry for the nitpicking but it is a network API and we don't want this to do anything surprising.",
            "commit_id": "b697e996d82ed34900510a82d5a50f6d47ab9c8c",
            "created_at": "2026-04-07T03:49:28Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -76,6 +84,13 @@ function M.request(url, opts, on_response)\n     vim.list_extend(args, { '--output', opts.outpath })\n   end\n \n+  if opts.headers then\n+    vim.validate('opts.headers', opts.headers, 'table', true)\n+    for key, value in pairs(opts.headers) do\n+      vim.list_extend(args, { '-H', key .. ': ' .. value })",
